                        <div class="text-zaffre h3 mb-0">so-sure help</div>
                        <h1 class="text-primary mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
                        <p class="mb-5">We all need a little extra info sometimes, that's why we've put together this handy FAQ section for you! Can't find what you're looking for? Then don't hesitate to ask via <a href="#" class="open-intercom">live chat</a> {{ support_hours }} or by emailing us at <a href="mailto:support@spam.so-sure.net" class="mailto append-email">support</a>.</p>

                        <h2 id="top-questions" class="text-primary mt-5 mb-4">Top Questions</h2>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Why should I use you? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>Unlike other insurers, we're less focused on profit, and more focused on giving customers value.  Our mission is to make insurance better and cheaper for honest people,  and that's why we've developed clever anti-fraud tech that makes your life easier. Plus we're the only insurer that gives you <a href="#social-insurance-and-reward-pot">money back</a>.</p>
                                        <ul class="mb-0">
                                            <li class="mb-2">Instant cover from purchase</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">We aim for 24-72 hour replacement or repair once your claim is approved</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">Hassle-Free Claims</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">Low excess from just &pound;50</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">Insure mobiles up to 3 years old</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">No proof of purchase required upfront, or at all when you use our anti-fraud technology</li>
                                            <li>Rewards when you and your connections don't claim - up to 80% of your premium back</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    How much is excess? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>Our excess is as low as &pound;50 for accidental damage and &pound;70 for loss &amp; theft when you validate your phone with our app.</p>
                                        <p>Download our app and prove to us your device is in good working order and the screen isn't cracked by taking a selfie of your phone!</p>
                                        <p><strong>Depending on your policy, validating your phone may be mandatory.</strong></p>
                                        <p class="mb-0">Excess levels vary by make, model and memory size and might be higher for latest, most-expensive new handsets.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    What is an IMEI number and how do I find out the IMEI of my mobile phone? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>The IMEI (International Mobile Equipment Identification) number of your mobile phone is a unique identification code that is specific to your mobile phone.  If you change your mobile phone, it is important that you call us so we can update your policy with the correct details.</p>
                                        <h4 class="h6 text-zaffre">For Android users:</h4>
                                        <p>The easiest way to find your phone’s IMEI number if you’re on an Android device is to simply dial <mark>*#06#</mark>.</p>
                                        <p>If you’re still having trouble, then you should be able to find it in <mark>Settings &gt; About phone &gt; Status &gt; IMEI information</mark>.</p>
                                        <p>Your serial number will be on the Status screen.</p>
                                        <p class="mb-0">If requested by support, you can take a screenshot on most Android phones by holding the volume down and the power buttons for 1-2 seconds. The screen should flash and the photo can be found in your photos app.</p>
                                        <h4 class="h6 text-zaffre">For iOS (Apple) users:</h4>
                                        <p>Unfortunately, as we need your serial number on iOS you can’t just dial a number (although dialing the same number as above will reveal your IMEI number).</p>
                                        <p>As such you can find both numbers by going to <mark>Settings &gt; General &gt; About</mark>.</p>
                                        <p>If you’re using our app (or if requested by support), you can take a screenshot by pressing the <mark>Sleep/Wake</mark> and <mark>Home</mark> buttons at the same time until you see the screen flash quickly.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Do you cover other gadgets like laptops? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        No, sorry we only cover mobile phone insurance.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    I bought a used phone/my friend gave me an older phone can I still insure it? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        Yes we are able to insure second-hand phones provided they are in full working condition, without any damage, and less than 3 years old.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Do you have a discount for annual payments? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        Yes! If you pay yearly, you get one month free. In addition to that, you can add money to your reward pot by connecting with friends and family to earn up to 80% cashback.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Is there an age limit on the mobile phone I want to insure? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        The phone you want to insure must be <mark>less than 3 years old</mark> from when your policy begins.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Can I insure a mobile phone I bought from eBay or another auction site? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>Yes, you can take out insurance on a <a href="{{ path('phone_insurance_second_hand') }}">second hand</a> phone.</p>
                                        <p class="mb-0">The phone bought needs to have originally been sold into the UK or European Union market prior your purchase (e.g. we don't insure models sold in China).</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Do you cover phones that have been purchased outside of the UK? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        We only cover phones where the original manufacturer sold that model in the United Kingdom or European Union.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Are the replacement handsets brand new? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        We know how we can get attached to our phones so we will repair where we can. If your approved claim requires a mobile phone replacement (e.g. Theft), we will do our best to replace it with an identical fully refurbished device. We normally can. However, should this not be possible we will replace it with a fully refurbished or new item of a comparable specification or the equivalent value. Please be aware that it may not always be possible to replace your mobile phone with the same colour.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    How long will this take to get my mobile device repaired? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        Your screen is cracked, no worries, we've got your back.
                                        We aim to repair your device within 24-72 hours once your claim is approved, however some repairs may take a little longer. Rest assured we are obsessed about getting you up and running quickly that's why it will be a few additional days compared to a few weeks with some of our competition.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    What is the warranty on refurbished devices? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p class="mb-0">All refurbished devices come with a warranty provided by the supplier of that refurbished phone. This warranty varies by device and supplier, but all phones come with a minimum warranty of three months and over 80% of supplied phones have a 12 month warranty.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 id="the-so-sure-app-and-pic-sure" class="text-primary mt-5 mb-4">The so-sure app</h2>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Where can I download the app? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>You can download the so-sure app from the Apple App store of the Google Play store, just click on the relevant store for you below:</p>
                                        <ul class="list-inline mb-0">
                                            <li class="list-inline-item">
                                                <a class="ga-outbound-click"
                                                   data-clicklabel="iTunes"
                                                   href="{{ apple_download('') }}"
                                                   target="_blank"
                                                   rel="noopener noreferrer">
                                                   <img src="{{ cdn_url }}/images/icons/app-store-original.svg" alt="Download so-sure on the App Store" /></a>
                                            </li>
                                            <li class="list-inline-item">
                                                <a class="ga-outbound-click"
                                                   data-clicklabel="PlayStore"
                                                   href="{{ google_download('') }}"
                                                   target="_blank"
                                                   rel="noopener noreferrer">
                                                   <img src="{{ cdn_url }}/images/icons/google-play-original.svg" alt="Get so-sure on Google Play" /></a>
                                            </li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Validate your phone with our app <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <ol class="mb-0">
                                            <li class="mb-2">Open the so-sure app</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">In the top left corner you will see 3 horizontal lines, this is the menu, tap this</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">In the open menu tap 'pic-sure validation'</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">In the next screen read the instructions and click start now</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">A pop-up will appear asking for permission to use the phones camera, tap 'OK'</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">On the next screen will be instructions on how to complete the process, tap 'NEXT' in the bottom right corner.</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">The new screen will describe what the QR code will do, when you understand tap 'NEXT' in the bottom right corner</li>
                                            <li class="mb-2">Then the QR code will appear on the screen and you will be able to take the picture in the mirror</li>
                                        </ol>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Handy tips for validating your phone <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>Hold your phone approximately 10cm/4in away from the mirror and keep it steady. Your phone will vibrate once the phone is in the correct position. Make sure to keep it still. When you feel a second vibration, the photo has been taken. Done.</p>
                                        <p>If you don’t feel the vibration, make minor adjustments to the position of the phone, go slowly back and forth, you can tilt the phone slightly as well. You should also see a little preview from the camera when the phone is hold up so make sure the camera is seeing the QR Code.</p>
                                        <p class="mb-0">Then review the photo that is displayed, ensure that your entire phone is visible and if it is submit the photo otherwise try the process again.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    How much is my excess if I validate? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>Our excess is as low as &pound;50 for accidental damage and &pound;70 for loss &amp; theft when you validate your phone with our app.</p>
                                        <p>Download our app and prove to us your device is in good working order and the screen isn't cracked by taking a selfie of your phone!</p>
                                        <p>So, if something unfortunate happens and you haven't validated your phone with our app you will need to pay up to &pound;100 extra for any loss, damage or theft claims.</p>
                                        <p class="mb-0">Excess levels vary by make, model and memory size and might be higher for latest, most-expensive new handsets.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    What happens if my device gets rejected? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>If your picture is rejected this is because your phone screen is damaged, or we cant see the picture clearly.  If it is clearly damaged your policy will be immediately cancelled as buying a insurance policy with a pre-damaged phone is a fraud and an offense.</p>
                                        <p class="mb-0">If we can't see the picture clearly you will get an invalid notification with feedback on what went wrong. You would then need to try again, making sure you are in a brightly lit room and your mirror and the lens of your phone is clean.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 id="social-insurance-and-reward-pot" class="text-primary mt-5 mb-4">Social Insurance &amp; Reward Pot</h2>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    What is the Reward Pot? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        <p>The reward pot is basically a <mark>group no claims bonus</mark>.  For each person that buys insurance with us and connects together, for example You buy a policy and invite your mum to buy.  She buys a policy and then you connect, each of you receive up to &pound;10 into your reward pots.</p>

                                        <div class="h4 text-zaffre">4 people connected to you = &pound;40 in your reward pot, £10 in each of theirs.</div>

                                        <div class="h4 text-zaffre">8 people connected = &pound;80 in your reward pot, £10 in each of theirs.</div>

                                        <p class="mb-0">If neither you nor your connected friends claim, we will payout to you the value of your reward pot at the end of the policy year.</p>

                                        {# TODO: When built #}
                                        {# <p>You can see our calculator here {insert new calculator}</p> #}
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Is the money back with the reward pot guaranteed? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
                                     itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                     itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                        It depends on if you and your social circle make a claim. If none of you claim the money is guaranteed, however if someone makes a claim there may be no money left in the reward pot.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="expanding-cardbox mb-4"
                             itemscope
                             itemprop="mainEntity"
                             itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <div class="expanding-cardbox__body">
                                <h3 class="h5 expanding-cardbox__title text-zaffre mb-0"
                                    itemprop="name">
                                    Can anyone connect to anyone? <i class="far fa-chevron-down text-dodger-blue fa-lg"></i>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="expanding-cardbox__expand mt-4"
                                     itemscope
